702738f-c.title: Brooklyn: 38th Street (East) - Avenue U
702738f-c.text:
(1)
East 38th Street, north from Ave. U, showing the Elisha Kimball
house, which, in 1919 was circled by a porch, and did not have the duser-
vation atop. It, probably, was added when the ''Sheepshead Bay Race
Track'' came into use.
August 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, looking south.
1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(3)
The same, remodeled, showing also, partially, homes facing Ave. U.
February 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
